	abstract = {The present system is a direct reading Solar Radiometer having integration facility. The solar radiations are trapped inside (Coated matt black) a copper sphere. The temperature rise of the copper sphere is measured by a linearised micro bead N.T.C thermistor. Its output voltage after linearization is fed to 3 1/2 digits A to D Converter with proper scale. This gives the direct solar radiation, alternatively the output can be fed to an electronic integrator having large time constant so that it can integrate heat radiation flux to a predetermined level and generate a pulse. The pulses generated due to solar radiation are counted by a small electromechanical counter. The total counts corrected for the calibration factor represented integrated heat radiation flux during the time of ergonomics studies. This small portable instrument can give the idea of radiative heat load during usual work and also its reduction attainable when sun shades or protectors are used for improvement of the working conditions. This low-cost battery powered prototype was constructed in the laboratory and the performance compared with other standard was found to be satisfactory.},
